[[File:Dan Habib TASH Annual Conference 3 Dec 2015.jpg|thumb|Dan Habib addressing [[TASH (organization)|TASH]]'s 40th Anniversary Annual Conference, Portland, Oregon, 3 December 2015]]

'''Daniel J. Habib''' is an [[United States|American]] documentary [[film director]], [[Film producer|producer]], and [[cinematographer]] based in [[Concord, New Hampshire]]. His award-winning films on disability-related topics include ''Who Cares About Kelsey?'', ''Including Samuel'', ''Restraint and Seclusion: Hear Our Stories'', and several short documentaries.<ref name="White House">{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2014/06/19/president-obama-announces-more-key-administration-posts|title=President Obama Announces More Key Administration Posts|work=Press release|publisher=The White House|accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref>

In 2014, he was named a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities by the Obama administration. Awards and honors for Habib include the Justice for All Grassroots Award from the [[American Association of People with Disabilities]] in 2013 and the Champion of Human and Civil Rights Award from the National Education Association (New Hampshire) in 2012.<ref name="White House"/>

