{{Incomplete list|date=June 2017}} This is a '''list of cities and towns founded by the Romans'''. It lists every city established and built by the [[Ancient Rome|ancient Romans]] to have begun as a [[Colonia (Roman)|colony]] often for the settlement of [[Roman citizenship|citizens]] or veterans of the [[Roman legion|legions]]. Many Roman colonies rose to become important commercial and cultural centers, transportation hubs and capitals of global empires. Most [[Europe|European towns]] still retain part of the original Roman street-grid.
